<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1965 Amendment</h4>
<p class="note-body">Section 105(b)(2) of <plaw congress="89" isprivate="false" number="117">Pub. L. 89–117,</plaw> as added by <plaw congress="89" isprivate="false" number="754">Pub. L. 89–754,</plaw> title X, §1001(3), Nov. 3, 1966, <statuteatlarge page="1284" volume="80">80 Stat. 1284</statuteatlarge>, provided that: “The interest rate provided by the amendment made in paragraph (1) [amending this section] shall be applicable (A) with respect to any loan made on or after August 10, 1965, and (B) with respect to any loan made prior to such date if construction of the housing or related facilities to be assisted by such loan was not commenced prior to such date, and not completed prior to the filing of an application for the benefits of such interest rate.”</p>
