<p class="note-body"><b>1974</b>—Subsec. (c)(1). <plaw congress="93" isprivate="false" number="383">Pub. L. 93–383,</plaw> §304(a)(1), struck out par. (1) which set forth limits on principal obligation of not to exceed $20,000,000, or not to exceed $50,000,000 if executed by a mortgagor under subsec. (b)(1) of this section.</p>
<p class="note-body">Subsec. (c)(3). <plaw congress="93" isprivate="false" number="383">Pub. L. 93–383,</plaw> §§303(a), 304(a)(2), substituted “$3,250” for “$2,500”, “$13,000” for “$9,900”, “$15,000” for “$11,550”, “$18,000” for “$13,750”, “$21,000” for “$16,500”, “$21,500” for “$16,500”, “$25,750” for “$19,800”, “$26,500” for “$20,350”, “$30,000” for “$23,100”, “$32,250” for “$24,750”, and “$36,465” for “$28,050”, and struck out limitation of $1,000,000 per mortgage for trailer courts or parks.</p>
