<p class="note-body"><b>1968</b>—Subsec. (c)(3). <plaw congress="90" isprivate="false" number="301">Pub. L. 90–301</plaw> limited interest rate on mortgages to such per centum per annum not in excess of 6 per centum as the Secretary finds necessary to meet the mortgage market.</p>
<p class="note-body"><b>1967</b>—<plaw congress="90" isprivate="false" number="19">Pub. L. 90–19</plaw> substituted “Secretary” for “Commissioner” wherever appearing in subsecs. (b), (b)(2), (c)(2), (3), (d), (e), (g), (h), (h)(1), (h)(2), (h)(2)(i), (j) to (<em>l</em>), (n), (<em>o</em>), and (r).</p>
<p class="note-body"><b>1965</b>—Subsec. (b). <plaw congress="89" isprivate="false" number="117">Pub. L. 89–117,</plaw> §1108(e)(4), substituted “General Insurance Fund” for “Housing Fund”.</p>
