<h4 class="note-head">References in Text</h4>
<p class="note-body"><uscode edition="2006" section="1720" title="12">Section 1720 of this title</uscode>, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(B)(i), was repealed by <plaw congress="98" isprivate="false" number="181">Pub. L. 98–181,</plaw> title IV, §483(a), Nov. 30, 1983, <statuteatlarge page="1240" volume="97">97 Stat. 1240</statuteatlarge>.</p>
<p class="note-body">Subsection (h) of <uscode edition="2006" section="1710" title="12">section 1710 of this title</uscode>, referred to in subsec. (e), was redesignated subsec. (i) by <plaw congress="105" isprivate="false" number="276">Pub. L. 105–276,</plaw> title VI, §602(1), Oct. 21, 1998, <statuteatlarge page="2674" volume="112">112 Stat. 2674</statuteatlarge>.</p>
<p class="note-body">Subsection (k) of <uscode edition="2006" section="1710" title="12">section 1710 of this title</uscode>, referred to in subsec. (e), was repealed by <plaw congress="105" isprivate="false" number="276">Pub. L. 105–276,</plaw> title VI, §601(c), Oct. 21, 1998, <statuteatlarge page="2673" volume="112">112 Stat. 2673</statuteatlarge>.</p>
<p class="note-body"><uscode edition="2006" section="8211" title="42">Section 8211 of title 42</uscode>, referred to in subsec. (p), was omitted from the Code pursuant to <uscode edition="2006" section="8229" title="42">section 8229 of Title 42</uscode>, The Public Health and Welfare, which terminated authority under that section on June 30, 1989.</p>
