<p class="note-body"><b>1969</b>—Subsec. (d)(2). <plaw congress="91" isprivate="false" number="152">Pub. L. 91–152,</plaw> §113(e)(1), (2), substituted “$18,000” for “$15,000”, “$21,000” for “$17,500”, wherever appearing, “$24,000” for “$20,000” wherever appearing, “$30,000” for “$25,000”, “$32,400” for “$27,000”, “$38,400” for “$32,000”, “$39,600” for “$33,000”, and “$45,600” for “$38,000”.</p>
